# ==============================================================================
# MOSUN OWO-ODUSI WEBSITE - ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# ==============================================================================

# MongoDB Configuration (REQUIRED)
# Get your MongoDB URI from MongoDB Atlas (https://cloud.mongodb.com)
# Or use local MongoDB: mongodb://localhost:27017/mosun-opportunities
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/mosun-opportunities?retryWrites=true&w=majority

# API Security (Optional)
# Used to protect /api/opportunities/refresh endpoint
# Default: mosun-refresh-2024
REFRESH_API_KEY=your-secure-api-key-here

# ==============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ==============================================================================
#
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
#    cp .env.local.example .env.local
#
# 2. MongoDB Setup (Required):
#    - Option A: MongoDB Atlas (Recommended - Free Tier Available)
#      * Sign up at https://cloud.mongodb.com
#      * Create a new cluster (free M0 tier)
#      * Click "Connect" -> "Connect your application"
#      * Copy the connection string
#      * Replace <password> with your database user password
#      * Update MONGODB_URI value above
#
#    - Option B: Local MongoDB
#      * Install MongoDB locally
#      * Use: MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/mosun-opportunities
#
# 3. Test the setup:
#    - Run: npm run dev
#    - Visit: http://localhost:3000/opportunities
#    - Data will auto-fetch from ReliefWeb API on first load
#
# ==============================================================================
# DATA SOURCE
# ==============================================================================
# 
# The system automatically fetches real opportunities from:
# - ReliefWeb Jobs API (No API key required)
#   https://api.reliefweb.int/v1/jobs
#
# Data is cached in MongoDB and refreshed every 24 hours automatically.
#
# ==============================================================================
# PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT (Vercel)
# ==============================================================================
#
# Add these environment variables in your Vercel project settings:
# 1. Go to Project Settings -> Environment Variables
# 2. Add MONGODB_URI with your MongoDB Atlas connection string
# 3. Add REFRESH_API_KEY with a secure random key (optional)
# 4. Deploy your project
#
# Vercel Cron Job (vercel.json) will automatically refresh data daily.
#
# ==============================================================================
